WEBVTT

00:06.484 --> 00:06.702
.

00:06.745 --> 00:08.182
- Previously on "Colony"...

00:08.225 --> 00:11.185
- Mr. Kynes specifically
assigned us to be your escort.

00:12.708 --> 00:13.187
- Trust me, Mr. Garland
is gonna keep me very safe.

00:14.840 --> 00:17.060
I ran into Will Bowman
last night. They abducted me.

00:18.714 --> 00:20.324
- Are you really comfortable
putting your life--

00:20.368 --> 00:22.065
our lives in the hands
of a guy like that?

00:22.109 --> 00:23.414
- Not this one again.
- Dad.

00:23.458 --> 00:25.199
- Hey, Sal.
This is Gracie.

00:25.242 --> 00:27.070
- I've been looking forward
to meeting you.

00:27.114 --> 00:29.507
- Every day I work for Kynes,
I get more intel.

00:29.551 --> 00:30.682
One of the Outliers
in my crew

00:30.726 --> 00:31.814
scouted the uptown facility.

00:31.857 --> 00:33.250
He wants to hit it.

00:33.294 --> 00:35.035
- Is it time to let them
have some guns?

00:38.908 --> 00:40.823
- I printed up this list
of the refugee camp.

00:40.866 --> 00:43.434
My husband is on it.
So are you.

00:43.478 --> 00:46.176
- If this checks out,
I'll be in touch.

00:46.220 --> 00:47.699
- Hey!

01:07.763 --> 01:10.809
[lock clicks,
chamber whooshes open]

03:18.546 --> 03:25.596
♪

04:02.372 --> 04:09.423
♪

04:28.920 --> 04:35.971
♪

05:02.519 --> 05:04.956
♪

05:08.003 --> 05:11.876
♪

05:14.923 --> 05:21.495
♪

05:30.852 --> 05:32.549
- I'm used to that.

05:32.593 --> 05:35.987
Today I actually had
a reason to get out of bed.

05:36.031 --> 05:38.120
- You still want to go
to the meet?

05:38.163 --> 05:40.078
- Hell, yes.

05:40.122 --> 05:43.821
You don't?

05:43.865 --> 05:47.651
- I worked so hard
to rebuild here.

05:47.695 --> 05:51.829
I mean, it's not much,
but it's something.

05:51.873 --> 05:54.832
- All we've built
is a distraction.

05:54.876 --> 05:56.399
It's like this Colony.

05:56.443 --> 05:57.835
Just bright and shiny enough

05:57.879 --> 05:59.837
to keep us
from wanting to dig any deeper.

05:59.881 --> 06:02.187
- I know.

06:02.231 --> 06:03.798
It's still a risk.

06:03.841 --> 06:06.670
We don't know anything
about these people.

06:06.714 --> 06:09.412
- We know
they're professionals...

06:09.456 --> 06:13.808
unlike any other cell
we've had to deal with.

06:16.550 --> 06:18.943
- This decision affects them.

06:18.987 --> 06:20.858
- Bram gets it.
- Gracie doesn't.

06:20.902 --> 06:22.904
- She just wants
a normal life.

06:22.947 --> 06:25.689
- I thought you would jump
at this chance--

06:25.733 --> 06:27.691
a real insurgency,

06:27.735 --> 06:29.563
one that's trained
and organized,

06:29.606 --> 06:31.086
one who can help us figure out
what's really going on.

06:31.129 --> 06:33.436
- A lot's changed, Will.

06:35.960 --> 06:37.571
- Yeah.

06:39.094 --> 06:40.791
Well...

06:40.835 --> 06:43.533
I'm going.

06:43.577 --> 06:45.535
[engine turning over
in the distance]

06:45.579 --> 06:48.712
- Okay.
So am I.

06:48.756 --> 06:51.715
I want to hear
what they have to say.

06:54.762 --> 07:01.072
♪

07:01.116 --> 07:04.075
[men grunting,
punches thudding]

07:04.119 --> 07:11.126
♪

07:30.667 --> 07:32.887
These are the guys
I was telling you about.

07:32.930 --> 07:34.236
This is Harris.

07:34.279 --> 07:36.107
- That's right.

07:36.151 --> 07:39.589
You guys know
a lot about us.

07:39.633 --> 07:40.895
I just want to know how.

07:40.938 --> 07:42.984
- I'm an Outlier.
So is he.

07:43.027 --> 07:44.159
Him, too.

07:44.202 --> 07:45.943
Same is probably true
for you

07:45.987 --> 07:49.686
and most of the folks
in this gym.

07:49.730 --> 07:50.861
- What the hell
is an Outlier?

07:50.905 --> 07:52.123
- Professionals--

07:52.167 --> 07:53.690
flagged and tracked
by the Occupation

07:53.734 --> 07:55.126
since before the Arrival.

07:55.170 --> 07:56.693
- I work
in the refugee camps.

07:56.737 --> 07:58.913
We identify Outliers
the moment they register

07:58.956 --> 08:02.133
and quietly relocate
them into the Colony.

08:04.571 --> 08:06.834
- The Occupation
is building an army.

08:06.877 --> 08:08.270
The Morks are on the run,

08:08.313 --> 08:10.098
fighting a war
against something else.

08:10.141 --> 08:12.796
That's why
they colonized us.

08:12.840 --> 08:14.537
And when their enemy
catches up to them,

08:14.581 --> 08:16.844
the Outliers are gonna be
their first line of defense.

08:16.887 --> 08:18.846
- We all thought
we survived the purge

08:18.889 --> 08:20.195
because we were smart.

08:20.238 --> 08:23.633
Turns out we're not
as clever as we thought.

08:23.677 --> 08:25.156
- I don't know.
I'm pretty clever.

08:26.897 --> 08:28.333
Occupation
made a big mistake

08:28.377 --> 08:30.161
putting you all
in the same Colony like this.

08:30.205 --> 08:33.904
We have an opportunity
to exploit it.

08:33.948 --> 08:37.125
Look, it seems
like a compelling story.

08:37.168 --> 08:40.998
How do I know
it's not just a fairy tale?

08:41.042 --> 08:44.611
- We abducted a high-level IGA
official and interrogated him.

08:48.266 --> 08:50.181
- We have the whole thing
on tape.

08:50.225 --> 08:52.009
- The answers
the official gave us

08:52.053 --> 08:54.142
fit with the intel
I collected in L.A.

08:54.185 --> 08:56.013
Classified
Occupation documents--

08:56.057 --> 08:59.800
they talk about building
a biological weapon in Seattle.

08:59.843 --> 09:02.672
- Some place safe.

09:02.716 --> 09:04.152
- Like she said,

09:04.195 --> 09:06.589
there's a lot of talented
people in this Colony.

09:06.633 --> 09:09.070
Put them together,
we could do some real damage.

09:11.072 --> 09:13.378
All right, I've got a contact
high in local authority.

09:13.422 --> 09:16.860
Give me a beat.
Let me verify it.

09:20.298 --> 09:22.300
- We're in business.

09:31.179 --> 09:36.750
♪

09:36.793 --> 09:39.013
- You look like a man
who's flush with information.

09:39.056 --> 09:41.145
- I was meeting
with one of the cells.

09:41.189 --> 09:43.887
They just recruited
some new members who claim

09:43.931 --> 09:47.108
to have recently captured
a high-level IGA official.

09:47.151 --> 09:48.239
- Snyder.

09:48.283 --> 09:50.285
- The other night at his hotel,

09:50.328 --> 09:51.939
me and Ford are watching him.

09:51.982 --> 09:53.636
He disappears for an hour.

09:53.680 --> 09:56.160
Comes back
with a bullshit story.

09:56.204 --> 09:57.684
- These new recruits,

09:57.727 --> 09:59.729
did they say
what Snyder gave up?

09:59.773 --> 10:02.123
- No details, but it's
about the Outlier program.

10:06.910 --> 10:08.825
I was getting tired
of that little rat

10:08.869 --> 10:10.087
running around my Colony.

10:10.131 --> 10:12.089
- Actually...

10:12.133 --> 10:14.744
he contacted me
last night...

10:14.788 --> 10:17.094
said he had something important
that I needed to see.

10:17.138 --> 10:19.096
- Then I think you should go
talk to the man.

10:19.140 --> 10:20.663
Don't let him know
what we know.

10:20.707 --> 10:22.665
Just ask him
some follow-up questions

10:22.709 --> 10:23.884
about his disappearance.

10:23.927 --> 10:26.234
Let him hang himself.

10:50.737 --> 10:52.869
- Funny, I thought you said
you were gonna be alone.

10:52.913 --> 10:54.392
- Forgive me.

10:56.177 --> 10:57.700
Some of my recent experiences

10:57.744 --> 11:00.964
have made me a bit less
trusting of people.

11:01.008 --> 11:04.359
- Oh, you mean like the girl
you paid to slap you around?

11:04.402 --> 11:05.752
- No.

11:05.795 --> 11:09.799
She delivered exactly
as advertised.

11:09.843 --> 11:11.758
- You said you had something
to talk about?

11:11.801 --> 11:13.107
- I'm afraid that was a lie.

11:13.150 --> 11:14.456
I asked you to meet

11:14.499 --> 11:17.241
because there's something
you can do for me.

11:39.873 --> 11:46.923
♪

12:01.111 --> 12:04.201
[boat horn blows
in the distance]

12:09.903 --> 12:11.905
- I'm hungry.

12:11.948 --> 12:14.211
- We still got
a couple hours to lunch.

12:14.255 --> 12:17.562
- Yeah, well,
tell that to my stomach.

12:21.305 --> 12:25.788
What the hell was that?
- An explosion.

12:25.832 --> 12:27.485
- To help.

12:41.108 --> 12:48.115
♪

13:03.608 --> 13:05.436
Hey.
You're gonna be okay.

13:05.480 --> 13:09.005
Stay with me, all right?

13:12.574 --> 13:12.966
.

13:28.242 --> 13:31.375
- Truck bomb.

13:33.029 --> 13:35.162
- Along with
a lot of other people.

13:35.205 --> 13:37.164
- I'm gonna have to report
this incident to Davos.

13:37.207 --> 13:39.079
- You do what you want to.

13:39.122 --> 13:41.168
- I'm just letting you know
that a team is likely to arrive

13:41.211 --> 13:45.128
to conduct
a full investigation.

13:45.172 --> 13:46.956
- We had a deal.

13:47.000 --> 13:48.566
The IGA doesn't get
to interfere in Seattle.

13:48.610 --> 13:50.177
- The terms of the deal

13:50.220 --> 13:52.092
were that the IGA
would stay out of Seattle

13:52.135 --> 13:54.659
provided that
you maintained control.

13:54.703 --> 13:57.358
It sure doesn't look
like control to me.

13:57.401 --> 14:01.449
[indistinct chatter continues,
fire extinguishers whooshing]

14:07.585 --> 14:09.413
- Harris isn't
answering his phone.

14:09.457 --> 14:10.675
You need to find him now.

14:10.719 --> 14:12.025
- I'll handle it.

14:12.068 --> 14:14.201
There's someone here
to see you...

14:14.244 --> 14:17.204
from the IGA.

14:19.554 --> 14:25.081
♪

14:27.257 --> 14:28.998
Helena.

14:31.261 --> 14:33.698
- How many Outliers
did we lose?

14:33.742 --> 14:35.178
- Three.

14:35.222 --> 14:37.354
- Mm.
This is a problem.

14:37.398 --> 14:40.444
You didn't waste
any time coming up here

14:40.488 --> 14:42.229
to dance on my grave.

14:42.272 --> 14:43.926
- I was touring our facility
in the Central Valley

14:43.970 --> 14:45.188
when I heard the news.

14:45.232 --> 14:47.408
It was a quick flight.

14:47.451 --> 14:50.454
- Your errand boy,
Alan Snyder--

14:50.498 --> 14:52.500
he's compromised.

14:53.980 --> 14:56.156
- He was abducted
by a Resistance group,

14:56.199 --> 14:58.245
which feels like something
he should've reported

14:58.288 --> 14:59.637
up the chain.

14:59.681 --> 15:02.336
I can only wonder
what he told them.

15:04.642 --> 15:07.297
- Well, I'm here
to talk about Seattle.

15:07.341 --> 15:09.212
- A model Colony.

15:09.256 --> 15:11.606
- It was.
- Nothing's changed.

15:11.649 --> 15:14.304
A day with one explosion
would be a great victory

15:14.348 --> 15:16.437
for your other Colonies.

15:16.480 --> 15:19.135
- Well, it wasn't
just an explosion.

15:19.179 --> 15:22.312
It was an attack
on a critical resource.

15:22.356 --> 15:24.097
Our Hosts
will have questions.

15:24.140 --> 15:26.621
- Which I will answer.

15:26.664 --> 15:29.058
I know why you
sent Snyder here.

15:29.102 --> 15:30.712
I know why you
jumped on a plane

15:30.755 --> 15:32.496
the moment you
heard the news.

15:32.540 --> 15:34.759
It's because you and the other
bureaucrats at the IGA

15:34.803 --> 15:36.413
hate what I'm doing

15:36.457 --> 15:40.026
because it doesn't fit
in your narrow little model.

15:40.069 --> 15:42.680
Thing is, I don't care.

15:42.724 --> 15:44.682
And you don't have the juice
to change anything.

15:44.726 --> 15:46.597
You might just get back
on your plane

15:46.641 --> 15:49.035
and take your errand boy
with you.

15:54.692 --> 15:57.217
- Alan.
- Helena.

16:03.701 --> 16:05.355
- This is about the convoy,
isn't it?

16:05.399 --> 16:07.009
- Outliers--
you killed Outliers.

16:07.053 --> 16:08.315
- Seems to be having
the desired effect.

16:08.358 --> 16:10.665
- I signed off
on a false-flag operation

16:10.708 --> 16:12.362
If our Hosts find out
about this--

16:12.406 --> 16:14.277
- A simple attack never
would have given us

16:14.321 --> 16:17.150
the necessary leverage, and
this was just the first step.

16:18.499 --> 16:20.762
- Kynes has been
reverse engineering

16:20.805 --> 16:23.460
our Host's technology.

16:23.504 --> 16:25.767
- You have no proof.
- But I know it's true.

16:25.810 --> 16:27.856
And once we have the authority
to look under every rock

16:27.899 --> 16:29.336
in this Colony,

16:29.379 --> 16:32.817
we'll find more than enough
to hang him.

16:32.861 --> 16:34.863
- Killing three Outliers
isn't gonna give the IGA

16:34.906 --> 16:36.647
the pretext it needs
to come in here.

16:36.691 --> 16:38.780
- You haven't seen
my second act yet.

16:42.566 --> 16:45.395
- Sometimes I miss
the old Alan...

16:45.439 --> 16:47.354
the one crippled
with self-doubt.

16:47.397 --> 16:49.443
- As I remember,
you fired that Alan,

16:49.486 --> 16:52.272
sent him to some godforsaken
processing facility

16:52.315 --> 16:55.449
outside of Los Angeles.

16:55.492 --> 16:58.147
- Live and learn.

16:58.191 --> 17:00.671
Kynes told me that, uh,

17:00.715 --> 17:04.414
you'd been abducted
by a Resistance cell.

17:08.549 --> 17:11.421
- I play all sides, Helena.

17:11.465 --> 17:13.728
That's my gift.

17:25.479 --> 17:32.529
♪

17:42.931 --> 17:45.238
- They found Harris, sir.

17:45.281 --> 17:48.241
[indistinct chatter
over police radio]

17:48.284 --> 17:52.245
♪

17:52.288 --> 17:54.290
- Forensics found
the remains of an IED

17:54.334 --> 17:56.858
in the back of the truck--
it detonated prematurely.

17:56.901 --> 17:58.729
- So we're supposed to believe

17:58.773 --> 18:01.602
that Harris attacked the convoy
then blew himself up

18:01.645 --> 18:04.257
en route to commit
another act of terror?

18:04.300 --> 18:06.955
- It doesn't add up.
- It's nonsense.

18:06.998 --> 18:09.175
They set him up.

18:11.568 --> 18:14.789
- I want an autopsy on him
as soon as possible.

18:14.832 --> 18:17.661
♪

18:20.273 --> 18:20.447
.

18:20.490 --> 18:22.405
- Here's the thing
I don't get.

18:23.319 --> 18:23.928
You snuck into this Colony,

18:25.016 --> 18:25.234
but me and the rest
of those guys

18:26.105 --> 18:26.496
came through the front door.

18:27.584 --> 18:28.194
- Why aren't you
in one of those pods?

18:29.369 --> 18:30.196
- Yeah.
- Maybe they're watching you.

18:30.239 --> 18:31.893
- Doesn't seem worth
the risk.

18:31.936 --> 18:33.938
They must know that if a couple
of us find each other,

18:33.982 --> 18:35.375
there's gonna be trouble.

18:35.418 --> 18:37.159
- They sure seemed to want you
in one of those pods

18:37.203 --> 18:39.074
back in L.A.
- Exactly.

18:39.118 --> 18:41.990
So what changed?
What's different about Seattle?

18:42.033 --> 18:44.993
And those pros you saw,
the ones who work for Kynes--

18:45.036 --> 18:47.213
maybe they're Outliers, too?

18:47.256 --> 18:48.823
- Could be.

19:06.275 --> 19:08.364
- Hi.

19:08.408 --> 19:10.497
- Hi.
Uh, can I help you?

19:12.281 --> 19:14.153
- This is my house.

19:17.156 --> 19:20.246
- Uh-huh.
- I'm Katie.

19:22.944 --> 19:24.293
Uh, Will's wife.

19:26.426 --> 19:27.992
- Oh.

19:28.036 --> 19:30.081
- You've already heard
that much about me, huh?

19:30.125 --> 19:32.388
- No, uh, nothing, really.

19:34.521 --> 19:36.262
- Okay.

19:36.305 --> 19:37.959
- I'm sorry.

19:38.002 --> 19:41.310
Um, can we start over?

19:44.183 --> 19:46.010
How's that?

19:46.054 --> 19:47.969
- Still a little awkward.

19:48.012 --> 19:50.885
- Right.

19:50.928 --> 19:52.626
- Uh, Will's here,
I'm guessing?

19:52.669 --> 19:54.454
- Yeah, he's inside
with Broussard.

19:54.497 --> 19:56.369
They're talking shop.

19:58.458 --> 20:00.373
- They do like
their boys' time.

20:00.416 --> 20:04.333
- Mm.

20:04.377 --> 20:06.553
- Did they meet
with the other cell?

20:06.596 --> 20:09.120
- We all did, yeah.

20:12.515 --> 20:14.952
- They seem professional.

20:16.302 --> 20:19.261
- I've learned
the hard way to, uh--

20:19.305 --> 20:22.395
to wait for people
to prove themselves.

20:25.615 --> 20:28.183
- Broussard said you were
with him at the beginning

20:28.227 --> 20:30.011
in L.A.

20:30.054 --> 20:32.231
- That was a long time ago.

20:33.493 --> 20:35.538
Do you have a family?

20:37.540 --> 20:40.456
- No.

20:40.500 --> 20:42.589
I was in L.A.
for a medical conference

20:42.632 --> 20:44.982
when the Arrival happened.

20:45.026 --> 20:46.288
So I'm alone.

20:49.596 --> 20:52.251
- Have you spent
a lot of time with Will?

20:53.991 --> 20:55.471
- Some.

21:05.568 --> 21:08.049
- He's been
through a lot.

21:08.092 --> 21:11.966
♪

21:12.009 --> 21:14.490
- Has he done anything
I should know about?

21:14.534 --> 21:19.626
♪

21:19.669 --> 21:22.106
- In my line of work,

21:22.150 --> 21:26.067
I'm in the proximity
of a lot of tragedy.

21:26.110 --> 21:28.461
Men and women usually
handle it differently.

21:30.724 --> 21:32.726
Guys like Will...

21:32.769 --> 21:36.338
tend to be
more action-oriented.

21:41.604 --> 21:44.215
- I'm sorry.

21:53.616 --> 21:57.272
♪

21:57.316 --> 21:59.274
What's going on?

21:59.318 --> 22:01.145
- Inside.

22:01.189 --> 22:08.239
♪

22:13.027 --> 22:16.247
- Stay where you are.

22:19.381 --> 22:21.427
- Harris is dead.

22:21.470 --> 22:24.386
- There was a bombing
downtown--a truck.

22:25.692 --> 22:27.781
- A transport
headed for Blake Island.

22:27.824 --> 22:30.305
It was carrying Outliers.

22:30.349 --> 22:32.786
- No, he was killed
in a second explosion.

22:32.829 --> 22:36.616
- You hear anything
about this at the hospital?

22:36.659 --> 22:38.139
- I had lunch with a friend.

22:38.182 --> 22:40.402
It must've happened
after my shift.

22:41.795 --> 22:43.623
- No.
- Wasn't ours either.

22:43.666 --> 22:45.320
- There hasn't been
a Resistance attack

22:45.364 --> 22:46.713
in this Colony
in 18 months,

22:46.756 --> 22:48.367
and then
you guys show up.

22:48.410 --> 22:50.107
- You think the four of us
have the muscle

22:50.151 --> 22:51.326
to pull off
something like this?

22:51.370 --> 22:53.067
- You tell me.

22:53.110 --> 22:55.417
- The IGA official we abducted

22:55.461 --> 22:58.638
said he came to Seattle
to find dirt on Kynes.

22:58.681 --> 23:00.727
The Authority is trying
to discredit him.

23:00.770 --> 23:03.425
- They're a military asset.

23:03.469 --> 23:05.645
Hitting them would attract
a lot of attention.

23:05.688 --> 23:07.821
- Why would the IGA
destroy their own assets?

23:07.864 --> 23:10.606
- The man
we're talking about...

23:10.650 --> 23:12.695
he's capable of anything.

23:12.739 --> 23:15.219
- Hmm.
I want to see the tape.

23:16.525 --> 23:18.571
- Fine.

23:32.149 --> 23:34.238
This...

23:34.282 --> 23:36.327
says that there's
a bio-weapons facility

23:36.371 --> 23:38.329
in Seattle.

23:38.373 --> 23:41.158
- We know more than you think.

23:41.202 --> 23:42.682
And if I catch you
in another lie,

23:42.725 --> 23:44.292
there won't be a warning.

23:44.335 --> 23:45.685
I will cut your throat,

23:45.728 --> 23:48.078
and you will bleed out
right here.

23:51.299 --> 23:53.214
- Alan Snyder--

23:53.257 --> 23:55.129
a bloc governor
from the Los Angeles Colony...

23:55.172 --> 23:56.652
until he got promoted.

23:56.696 --> 23:58.828
- Before the Arrival,

23:58.872 --> 24:01.483
our Hosts used an algorithm
to sort humans

24:01.527 --> 24:03.093
into different groups.

24:03.137 --> 24:05.444
Your group
determined your fate--

24:05.487 --> 24:07.881
whether you worked for the IGA
or went to the Factory

24:07.924 --> 24:09.709
or lived in the Green Zone.

24:09.752 --> 24:13.495
Everything was based
on how you were classified.

24:13.539 --> 24:16.150
- So Outliers are
one of these groups?

24:17.630 --> 24:20.502
- A special group
with special privileges.

24:22.156 --> 24:23.723
- That's why we came to you.

24:23.766 --> 24:26.160
We need to work together
to figure that out.

24:26.203 --> 24:29.555
- Harris was
your commander, right?

24:29.598 --> 24:31.600
I know it's hard
to lose him,

24:31.644 --> 24:34.560
but it's next man up.

24:34.603 --> 24:37.476
And you've got to realize
we aren't the enemy.

24:42.306 --> 24:44.352
- I need to call someone.

24:45.614 --> 24:48.399
They do not move
until I get back.

24:59.193 --> 24:59.367
.

25:05.068 --> 25:07.244
- Hey.

25:07.288 --> 25:08.768
I didn't know you were here.

25:08.811 --> 25:12.293
- Yeah, I was one
of the first responders.

25:13.903 --> 25:15.296
- Yeah, I'm fine.

25:15.339 --> 25:17.124
'Cause I don't
think I'll be getting

25:17.167 --> 25:18.821
much sleep tonight.

25:20.823 --> 25:22.869
- I'm just worried
about Gracie.

25:22.912 --> 25:24.392
School?

25:24.435 --> 25:26.133
- Yeah, they're on lockdown.
I checked.

25:26.176 --> 25:28.483
- That's the safest place
to be. I mean, this--

25:28.527 --> 25:30.050
this was
a professional job.

25:30.093 --> 25:33.314
They're not going after kids.

25:33.357 --> 25:36.970
Meadow says you take good care
of your sister.

25:37.013 --> 25:40.147
- She's been through a lot.

25:40.190 --> 25:42.453
- As you have,
I'm guessing.

25:44.804 --> 25:46.501
You know,
the wife and I were talking

25:46.545 --> 25:48.155
about how much fun it was

25:48.198 --> 25:49.983
to have you and Gracie over
for dinner,

25:50.026 --> 25:52.376
and I think
you should come again.

25:52.420 --> 25:53.900
- Okay.

25:53.943 --> 25:55.249
- Soon.

26:06.129 --> 26:08.958
- Harris was dead
before that bomb went off.

26:09.002 --> 26:10.873
- Sloppy...

26:10.917 --> 26:13.354
almost like they don't care
that we know.

26:13.397 --> 26:15.486
It's no coincidence
our problems began

26:15.530 --> 26:17.880
shortly after Alan Snyder
arrived in this bloc.

26:17.924 --> 26:20.013
Question is
how high it goes.

26:20.056 --> 26:21.841
Get me
the airport director.

26:21.884 --> 26:23.103
- Yes, sir.

26:26.236 --> 26:28.021
You're on
with Garvey McCallum.

26:28.064 --> 26:29.718
- Hey, Garvey, it's Everett.

26:29.762 --> 26:31.415
I have a question
about Helena Goldwyn's flight.

26:31.459 --> 26:33.113
Where'd she come from?

26:33.156 --> 26:34.854
- Well, the manifest
said our facility

26:34.897 --> 26:36.203
in the Central Valley.

26:37.944 --> 26:40.033
- But there was a second
passenger on the plane--

26:40.076 --> 26:42.949
an IGA courier headed out
to the island.

26:42.992 --> 26:44.428
- And they only come
from Davos.

26:44.472 --> 26:45.995
- Yeah.

26:46.039 --> 26:47.997
- Thanks, Garvey.
- No problem.

26:50.130 --> 26:54.438
- She was already in the air
when the bomb went off.

26:54.482 --> 26:57.398
- Helena's too political
to do anything on her own.

27:00.619 --> 27:03.143
The entire IGA
is gunning for me.

27:03.186 --> 27:06.973
I thought we had more time,
but it is what it is.

27:09.192 --> 27:11.064
Glen.
- Yes, sir.

27:11.107 --> 27:14.589
- Send an encrypted SMS
to everyone in Project Phoenix.

27:14.633 --> 27:16.547
Let them know
we've just gone live.

27:16.591 --> 27:18.941
- Yes, sir.

27:21.988 --> 27:25.905
♪

27:25.948 --> 27:28.255
- Hey.

27:28.298 --> 27:31.388
♪

27:33.956 --> 27:35.610
Shut it down.

27:35.654 --> 27:38.439
♪

27:41.964 --> 27:43.966
- It's a shame to kill
something this beautiful,

27:44.010 --> 27:46.099
but...

27:46.142 --> 27:49.102
we always knew
this was temporary.

27:49.145 --> 27:50.451
- All right.

27:50.494 --> 27:57.545
♪

28:05.335 --> 28:08.861
It's been a pleasure, Ev.

28:08.904 --> 28:11.298
See you
on the other side, huh?

28:11.341 --> 28:13.474
- I hope so.

28:13.517 --> 28:20.568
♪

28:30.970 --> 28:33.363
If it isn't the Ice Queen
and her evil little sidekick.

28:33.407 --> 28:34.974
- We need to speak with you.

28:35.017 --> 28:36.453
- I'd love to,
but I'm late for a meeting.

28:36.497 --> 28:39.108
- We ran tests on your
deceased bodyguard, Harris.

28:39.152 --> 28:42.546
It seems he was designated
as an Outlier.

28:44.244 --> 28:45.506
- Do you know
the difference

28:45.549 --> 28:47.334
between intelligence
and cunning?

28:47.377 --> 28:49.684
Of course not,
because if you did,

28:49.728 --> 28:51.512
they never would
have picked you.

28:51.555 --> 28:53.383
- You're about to pay the price
for your arrogance.

28:53.427 --> 28:54.994
- And when do you
pay the price

28:55.037 --> 28:57.518
for selling out
your whole species?

28:57.561 --> 28:59.302
I can't even blame you.

28:59.346 --> 29:01.043
This is what happens
when you give

29:01.087 --> 29:02.958
large power
to small minds.

29:03.002 --> 29:05.047
- Those small minds
are going to bring you down.

29:05.091 --> 29:06.919
- Just like our Hosts wanted.

29:06.962 --> 29:08.398
Why do you think

29:08.442 --> 29:11.010
they put the morally bankrupt
administrator

29:11.053 --> 29:14.013
of a shitty community college
in charge of a bloc?

29:14.056 --> 29:17.016
Or a failed studio exec
in charge of a Colony?

29:17.059 --> 29:18.582
- They saw our potential.

29:18.626 --> 29:20.541
- They saw weakness.

29:20.584 --> 29:22.456
They knew you were
the kind of crabs

29:22.499 --> 29:24.153
who would always drag
the others

29:24.197 --> 29:25.894
back down
into the bucket.

29:25.938 --> 29:26.982
- Oh.

29:29.071 --> 29:31.030
- Harris was my friend.

29:31.073 --> 29:37.601
♪

29:40.648 --> 29:40.996
.

29:53.052 --> 29:55.750
- I left word.

29:55.794 --> 29:58.231
Phone crashed
before he could call me back.

29:58.274 --> 29:59.928
Let me see yours.

30:02.583 --> 30:05.455
It's dead, too.

30:05.499 --> 30:07.762
- Mine too.

30:07.806 --> 30:11.244
- Is that because
of the attack?

30:12.332 --> 30:14.421
- It's a signal.

30:17.990 --> 30:20.079
- Harris said if the network
ever went down,

30:20.122 --> 30:22.168
we should meet
at a rally point

30:22.211 --> 30:24.257
and be ready
for something big.

30:24.300 --> 30:26.346
- How would he know
the network might go down?

30:26.389 --> 30:28.478
- He had inside information.

30:30.741 --> 30:34.180
Harris worked for Kynes.

30:34.223 --> 30:36.660
- It's how we got our intel.

30:36.704 --> 30:38.532
- How do you know Harris
wasn't a double agent?

30:38.575 --> 30:40.273
- I don't.

30:40.316 --> 30:41.665
- If the phone's a signal,

30:41.709 --> 30:43.232
you need to get
to that rally point,

30:43.276 --> 30:44.451
and we're coming with you.

30:44.494 --> 30:46.279
- No.

30:46.322 --> 30:47.758
We have protocols.

30:47.802 --> 30:50.979
- Your protocols died
with Harris.

30:55.331 --> 30:56.724
- Fine.

30:56.767 --> 30:58.247
You two come with me.

30:58.291 --> 31:02.251
They stay here
with the rest of my guys.

31:09.606 --> 31:12.044
- All right.

31:18.702 --> 31:20.704
- Well, this seems like
a pretty stupid idea.

31:20.748 --> 31:22.489
What do you think?

31:22.532 --> 31:26.536
Nobody asked me what I think.

31:26.580 --> 31:28.756
- I'm not authorized
to access the system.

31:28.799 --> 31:30.323
- We're giving you
the authorization.

31:30.366 --> 31:32.238
- That has to come
from Mr. Kynes.

31:32.281 --> 31:34.849
- Mr. Kynes works for the IGA,
which means he works for us,

31:34.893 --> 31:37.243
which means you work for us.

31:37.286 --> 31:39.288
- I'm really not comfortable
with this.

31:39.332 --> 31:41.073
- Access the system,

31:41.116 --> 31:43.510
or the next job you'll be
working will be reception

31:43.553 --> 31:46.687
at the Arctic fabrication
facility.

31:46.730 --> 31:49.037
What do you need?

31:49.081 --> 31:50.691
- This bloc runs
on information.

31:50.734 --> 31:52.171
We want it.

31:52.214 --> 31:54.216
Start by locating Harris
in the database.

31:54.260 --> 31:56.523
I need to know how many
trained killers like him

31:56.566 --> 31:58.786
are running around Seattle.

32:04.226 --> 32:05.706
- It's not working.

32:05.749 --> 32:07.621
- Glen.
- I swear.

32:07.664 --> 32:09.318
It's like
the whole system is down.

32:09.362 --> 32:11.233
The server has,
like, four backups.

32:11.277 --> 32:13.148
It's supposed
to be foolproof.

32:13.192 --> 32:14.367
- Find Kynes now.

32:14.410 --> 32:16.064
- I can't track his cell phone

32:16.108 --> 32:17.457
without logging
into the system.

32:17.500 --> 32:18.806
- Then call him.

32:21.765 --> 32:25.639
- Um, it looks
like this is down, too.

32:31.906 --> 32:34.561
- I think Mr. Kynes
has left the building.

32:37.607 --> 32:41.220
♪

32:41.263 --> 32:42.917
- Closed up tight.

32:42.961 --> 32:44.397
Even if we did
a walk-around,

32:44.440 --> 32:47.530
we probably
wouldn't see anything.

32:47.574 --> 32:50.229
- The light...

32:50.272 --> 32:52.448
that's the signal
for all clear.

32:52.492 --> 32:55.451
- Then I guess we have
nothing to worry about.

32:55.495 --> 33:02.371
♪

33:11.206 --> 33:12.860
- I'm going.

33:15.254 --> 33:16.951
- I'm with you.

33:16.995 --> 33:24.176
♪

33:44.587 --> 33:48.939
[O'Neill knocking code
on door]

33:48.983 --> 33:53.335
♪

33:53.379 --> 33:56.208
- I'm O'Neill.

33:56.251 --> 33:59.298
New guys,
but Harris vetted them.

33:59.341 --> 34:06.392
♪

34:12.746 --> 34:19.796
♪

34:26.542 --> 34:29.850
All right, listen up.

34:31.721 --> 34:33.767
My name is Adam Ford.

34:35.290 --> 34:38.467
Some of you reported
to my partner Harris.

34:38.511 --> 34:40.339
When we recruited you,
Harris and I told you

34:40.382 --> 34:42.341
that we worked
for Everett Kynes,

34:42.384 --> 34:44.865
but what we didn't tell you is
that you all work for him, too.

34:44.908 --> 34:47.259
- I'm not working
for a collaborator.

34:49.826 --> 34:51.524
- Mr. Kynes
saved your life.

34:51.567 --> 34:54.875
The same is true
for everyone in this room.

34:54.918 --> 34:58.313
If you are here,
that means you are an Outlier,

34:58.357 --> 34:59.923
which means
the Morks selected you

34:59.967 --> 35:02.448
to be part
of their slave army--

35:02.491 --> 35:04.363
some sacrificial first wave

35:04.406 --> 35:06.365
to be thrown
against their enemies.

35:06.408 --> 35:08.802
We should all be
in pods right now,

35:08.845 --> 35:10.891
waiting for our chance to die.

35:10.934 --> 35:13.763
But Mr. Kynes
put himself at risk

35:13.807 --> 35:16.723
and concealed us all
from the IGA.

35:16.766 --> 35:18.290
Now, a war is coming,

35:18.333 --> 35:20.944
and our planet is gonna be
the battlefield.

35:20.988 --> 35:24.034
The loser will fall,
the winner will go back home,

35:24.078 --> 35:25.906
and the collaborators
in the Global Authority

35:25.949 --> 35:28.735
think that they
will inherit the Earth.

35:28.778 --> 35:31.651
Mr. Kynes has
a different vision.

35:33.435 --> 35:36.046
The past 18 months, he's been
converting this Colony

35:36.090 --> 35:37.787
into a kind of ark.

35:37.831 --> 35:39.833
He's carefully selected
the population

35:39.876 --> 35:41.487
for the best
and brightest--

35:41.530 --> 35:43.532
scientists,
engineers, doctors,

35:43.576 --> 35:46.753
educators, soldiers.

35:46.796 --> 35:49.582
So, when this war is over,

35:49.625 --> 35:51.584
Seattle is gonna be
ground zero

35:51.627 --> 35:54.413
for the reboot
of human civilization.

35:54.456 --> 35:58.765
This is the beginning
of the real Resistance...

35:58.808 --> 36:00.941
the human Resistance.

36:03.987 --> 36:09.079
♪

36:58.651 --> 36:58.912
.

37:13.361 --> 37:15.537
I tried to get to school
before they released everybody

37:15.581 --> 37:17.626
but they kept me late
at work.

37:22.675 --> 37:24.285
Sorry.

37:24.329 --> 37:26.983
I kept trying to call.

37:27.027 --> 37:29.377
- Phones are dead.
It's weird.

37:29.421 --> 37:32.075
- I know.

37:35.078 --> 37:37.777
- I'm not sure.

37:37.820 --> 37:40.562
But we're safe here.

37:40.606 --> 37:42.738
- Do you have to go
back to work?

37:42.782 --> 37:43.739
- No.

37:43.783 --> 37:45.480
Not tonight.

37:51.094 --> 37:53.619
- It's expired.

37:53.662 --> 37:56.404
It's okay. I like it this way.
- No, it's not okay.

37:56.448 --> 37:57.927
You shouldn't have
to eat your cereal

37:57.971 --> 37:59.581
without your freakin' milk.

38:04.804 --> 38:07.850
[engine turning over
in the distance]

38:10.462 --> 38:13.508
- I know why Mom and Dad don't
like being around anymore.

38:15.815 --> 38:18.905
Because I make them
think about Charlie.

38:27.827 --> 38:29.698
I miss him.

38:31.700 --> 38:33.354
- Me too.

38:40.100 --> 38:41.667
It's gonna get better.

38:43.538 --> 38:45.323
- Yeah.

38:47.020 --> 38:50.545
Let's get out of here.

38:50.589 --> 38:53.418
- Meadow's house.

38:53.461 --> 38:56.508
Her dad invited us over
for dinner again.

38:56.551 --> 38:58.336
- I like them.

38:59.511 --> 39:01.730
- So do I.

39:01.774 --> 39:03.863
Go get your jacket.

39:03.906 --> 39:05.386
- Okay.

39:20.575 --> 39:22.403
- I do.

39:22.447 --> 39:25.363
It fits with everything
we've found so far.

39:29.105 --> 39:31.456
You ready to trust someone
you've never met?

39:31.499 --> 39:33.980
I don't know.

39:34.023 --> 39:36.635
But he's the enemy
of our enemy.

39:36.678 --> 39:38.550
And I'd rather be fighting
with the Outliers

39:38.593 --> 39:39.986
than against them.

39:42.684 --> 39:45.470
- So you're signing on.

39:45.513 --> 39:47.080
- I am.

39:54.914 --> 39:56.959
- I want to be
a part of it.

39:59.484 --> 40:01.834
I was lost for a long time.

40:01.877 --> 40:04.793
But then hiking up
the coast with you...

40:06.795 --> 40:09.537
I found purpose again.

40:11.626 --> 40:14.803
Even when you made me swim
in that freezing river.

40:21.767 --> 40:24.639
- That'll seem like bath water
compared to what's coming.

40:26.119 --> 40:27.816
- I understand the risks.

40:31.211 --> 40:38.174
♪

40:44.529 --> 40:48.010
- I don't suppose they found
Kynes hiding under some rock.

40:48.054 --> 40:50.491
- Not yet, no.

40:50.535 --> 40:53.233
- He's out there,
plotting something.

40:53.276 --> 40:55.496
- Well, that seems
unduly pessimistic.

40:55.540 --> 40:57.106
Maybe he knew
that we were coming for him

40:57.150 --> 40:58.586
and he decided to run.

40:58.630 --> 41:00.936
- Then why pull down
your whole network?

41:00.980 --> 41:03.069
He wants us to be blind.

41:03.112 --> 41:04.766
- Or maybe it was spite.

41:06.812 --> 41:08.944
Regaining control
won't be easy.

41:08.988 --> 41:12.948
But the IGA understands
how important Seattle is.

41:12.992 --> 41:15.560
They don't want
this Colony to fail.

41:15.603 --> 41:18.127
- I'm needed back in Davos.

41:18.171 --> 41:20.521
Kynes still has his allies,

41:20.565 --> 41:22.784
and it will need to be
explained to our Hosts.

41:22.828 --> 41:25.526
- Who are they sending
to run the Colony?

41:29.138 --> 41:30.662
- No.

41:30.705 --> 41:32.968
- This is
a critical situation, Alan.

41:33.012 --> 41:35.014
You're the only one
I can trust to handle it.

41:35.057 --> 41:37.059
- Is that a compliment
or the kiss of death?

41:37.103 --> 41:39.845
- Well, we can argue
about it all you want,

41:39.888 --> 41:41.803
but you really
don't have a choice.

41:41.847 --> 41:44.153
They picked you.

41:44.197 --> 41:46.939
You decided to come back,

41:46.982 --> 41:50.029
and you made the mistake
of being good.

41:52.335 --> 41:54.076
Good luck.

41:59.038 --> 42:06.088
♪

42:27.936 --> 42:31.984
♪
